EXTRACTED VALUE: Enemy Territory: Quake Wars isn't a bad game, it just fails to do anything to make you stand up and pay attention.
Turok manages to revive the ailing franchise. The dinosaurs look awesome and fighting them is just as cool.
Even with great multiplayer the rest of the game is brought down by some major design flaws that mostly occur in the single player campaign.
Instead of yesterday’s news, it’d be nice to see a high resolution, high definition 2D fighter on XBLA instead of ancient blocky sprites.
Disappointing that the 360 edition isn't visually distinct from the last-gen versions. [Issue #3]
Like the previous Def jams, Icon can't decide what kind of game it wants to be. [Apr 2007, p.88]
